20  , in some situations we might like to have our \"own\" `copyfile` which performs similarly to git-annex internal copy using `--reflink=auto` so the `copy` takes advantage of possibly supported by filesystem CoW.\r\n\r\nin current codebase we seems to not rely on it much\r\n```shell\r\n$> git grep -p copyfile            \r\ndatalad/cmd.py=def link_file_load(src, dst, dry_run=False):\r\ndatalad/cmd.py:        shutil.copyfile(src_realpath, dst)\r\ndatalad/metadata/aggregate.py=def _dump_extracted_metadata(agginto_ds, aggfrom_ds, db, to_save, force_extraction):\r\ndatalad/metadata/aggregate.py:            shutil.copyfile(\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py=from os.path import exists\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py:from shutil import copyfile\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py=def test_AnnexRepo_addurl_to_file_batched(sitepath, siteurl, dst):\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py:    copyfile(opj(sitepath, 'about.txt'), opj(dst, testfile))\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py:    copyfile(opj(sitepath, 'about2.txt'), opj(dst, testfile2))\r\ndatalad/support/tests/test_annexrepo.py:    copyfile(opj(sitepath, 'about2_.txt'), opj(dst, testfile2_))\r\n```\r\nbut in the context of datalad-container might come real handy", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2953/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2953/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}